<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF208-218-131  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 218 131.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Newsbytes  Oct 24 1989* Full Text COPYRIGHT Newsbytes Inc. 1989.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>SGA Pacific strengthens General Automation in the region.andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>Cameron, Keith.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   General Automation Inc. (Skokie, Illinois) (acquisitions andmergers)AWA Computers (acquisitions and mergers).andO;Ticker:    GA.andO;Topic:     Computer industryAcquisitionAustralia.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>SGA PACIFIC STRENGTHENS GENERAL AUTOMATION IN THE REGION SINGAPORE, SOUTHEASTASIA, 1989 OCT 15 (NB) -- The recent announcement by General Automation (GA)of the completion of the acquisition of AWA Computers, a major Australianplayer in the PICK Systems market, has been received well by regionalcustomers and prospects.andM;GA, under the leadership Asia and GA veteran, Carlton J. Parker, hasestablished itself soundly in Singapore with a number of substantial systemsin Government and the private sector.andP;  More recently, since GA acquired theMaxial Hotel Management System, Mr Parker has been seen regularly atcompleting and supporting sales throughout the region, particularly inHongkong and Taiwan.andM;The combined resources of GA, AWA and Sandersons Electronics of the UK nowprovides Mr Parker, who has now been appointed managing director of PacificOperations, with the facilities to expand dramatically on the base he hasestablished.andP;  It is expected that the recently opened Hongkong office will bebeefed up considerably to cater for the burgeoning PICK marketplace there.andM;(Keith Cameron/19891020)</TEXT></DOC>